# Public build-time config for the web app. ONLY NEXT_PUBLIC_-prefixed vars
# are inlined into the browser bundle, and ONLY non-secret, publicly-shippable
# values belong here — never an API key, token, or password (the bundle is
# served to every visitor). Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) to override.

# Backend origin the api-client prepends to every request.
#
# DEV: leave EMPTY. An empty base URL makes the client issue same-origin
# relative URLs (`/auth/login`) that next.config.ts's dev rewrites forward to
# the compose backend (see NEXT_DEV_API_PROXY there) — the same-origin path
# cookie-mode auth needs so the backend's SameSite=Lax cookies attach.
#
# PROD: set to the API origin ONLY if the API is served from a different origin
# than this app AND that origin returns credentialed CORS naming this app's
# origin (Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true, explicit origin, never `*`).
# The simpler prod posture is to keep it EMPTY and route `/api/*` (or the API
# paths) to the backend at the edge (e.g. a load balancer / CDN rule) so the
# browser stays same-origin and no cross-origin CORS/cookie dance is needed.
# See docs/fragment.md's Deployment section (added by sub-agent D).
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=
